(34, 'Routing and switching MIT CONTENT', '<h4 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 1.5rem; color: #212529; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, \'Noto Sans\', sans-serif, \'Apple Color Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Symbol\', \'Noto Color Emoji\'; background-color: #ffffff;\">TCP/IP layers</h4>\r\n<ol style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #212529; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, \'Noto Sans\', sans-serif, \'Apple Color Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Symbol\', \'Noto Color Emoji\'; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;\">Application layer:</span>messages + programs interfaces use this (application +prsentation+session) ie http,ftp etc</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;\">transport layer:</span>&nbsp;add headers and connection status, ie port numbers</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;\">network layer:</span>&nbsp;ip address, use Router</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;\">datalink layer:</span>&nbsp;use mac address on switch</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;\">physical layer:</span>&nbsp;binary maked to travel on wires</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><span class=\"text-danger\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder; color: #dc3545 !important;\">Every card (Bluetooth ,wifi) has its individual mac address</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"text-success\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder; color: #28a745 !important;\">A pc use all 5 layers so it can be maked router or switch</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h4 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 1.5rem; color: #212529; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, \'Noto Sans\', sans-serif, \'Apple Color Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Symbol\', \'Noto Color Emoji\'; background-color: #ffffff;\">Switching</h4>\r\n<h5 class=\"text-success\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 1.25rem; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, \'Noto Sans\', sans-serif, \'Apple Color Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Symbol\', \'Noto Color Emoji\'; background-color: #ffffff; color: #28a745 !important;\">Networks</h5>\r\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #212529; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, \'Noto Sans\', sans-serif, \'Apple Color Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Symbol\', \'Noto Color Emoji\'; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;\">broadcast:</span>&nbsp;send info one to all other i.e send sms to all world</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;\">multicast:&nbsp;</span>send one to more than one ie group sms</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;\">unicast:</span>&nbsp;sned info one to one ie chat with friend</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;\">anycast:</span>&nbsp;used in routers?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h5 class=\"text-success\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 1.25rem; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, \'Noto Sans\', sans-serif, \'Apple Color Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Symbol\', \'Noto Color Emoji\'; background-color: #ffffff; color: #28a745 !important;\">Bus topology</h5>\r\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #212529; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, \'Noto Sans\', sans-serif, \'Apple Color Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Symbol\', \'Noto Color Emoji\'; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder;\">Wired:&nbsp;</span>CSMA/CD?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 1.5rem; color: #212529; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, \'Noto Sans\', sans-serif, \'Apple Color Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Symbol\', \'Noto Color Emoji\'; background-color: #ffffff;\">Network Cores</h4>\r\n<dl style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #212529; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, \'Noto Sans\', sans-serif, \'Apple Color Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Emoji\', \'Segoe UI Symbol\', \'Noto Color Emoji\'; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\">\r\n<dt style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">Network Edges</dt>\r\n<dd style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; margin-left: 0px;\">end points,ie Sender &amp; receiver for example ATM,</dd>\r\n<dt style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">Network Cores:</dt>\r\n<dd style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; margin-left: 0px;\">Intermediat devices amoung edges ie switch,hub,router.</dd>\r\n<dt style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">Circut switching:</dt>\r\n<dd style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; margin-left: 0px;\">Communication that have&nbsp;<kbd style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, \'Liberation Mono\', \'Courier New\', monospace; font-size: 14px; padding: 0.2rem 0.4rem; color: #ffffff; background-color: #212529; border-radius: 0.2rem;\" title=\"direct link of two devices,no sharing amoung many devices\">dedicated link</kbd></dd>\r\n<dt style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">packet switching</dt>\r\n<dd style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; margin-left: 0px;\">use&nbsp;<kbd style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, \'Liberation Mono\', \'Courier New\', monospace; font-size: 14px; padding: 0.2rem 0.4rem; color: #ffffff; background-color: #212529; border-radius: 0.2rem;\" title=\"ie multiplexing\">shared link</kbd>&nbsp;for communication</dd>\r\n<dt style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">Physical communication</dt>\r\n<dd style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; margin-left: 0px;\">That use network (IP) + datalink (mac) + physical layer.</dd>\r\n<dt style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">Logical communication</dt>\r\n<dd style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; margin-left: 0px;\">that uses transport (for port) &amp; application layer (for url).</dd>\r\n<dt style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">To send email following protocols used</dt>\r\n<dd style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; margin-left: 0px;\"><kbd style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, \'Liberation Mono\', \'Courier New\', monospace; font-size: 14px; padding: 0.2rem 0.4rem; color: #ffffff; background-color: #212529; border-radius: 0.2rem;\" title=\"to send email\">SMTP</kbd>&nbsp;&rarr;&nbsp;<kbd style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, \'Liberation Mono\', \'Courier New\', monospace; font-size: 14px; padding: 0.2rem 0.4rem; color: #ffffff; background-color: #212529; border-radius: 0.2rem;\" title=\"file attachement\">FTP</kbd>&nbsp;&rarr;&nbsp;<kbd style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, \'Liberation Mono\', \'Courier New\', monospace; font-size: 14px; padding: 0.2rem 0.4rem; color: #ffffff; background-color: #212529; border-radius: 0.2rem;\" title=\"for transfer of data\">TCP/UDP</kbd>&nbsp;&rarr;&nbsp;<kbd style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, \'Liberation Mono\', \'Courier New\', monospace; font-size: 14px; padding: 0.2rem 0.4rem; color: #ffffff; background-color: #212529; border-radius: 0.2rem;\" title=\"routing\">IP</kbd></dd>\r\n<dt style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">Data link layer connectives</dt>\r\n<dd style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; margin-left: 0px;\"><kbd style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, \'Liberation Mono\', \'Courier New\', monospace; font-size: 14px; padding: 0.2rem 0.4rem; color: #ffffff; background-color: #212529; border-radius: 0.2rem;\" title=\"sublayer of datalink layer for data transfer\">Upper:</kbd>Logical Link control (LLC)&nbsp;<kbd style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, \'Liberation Mono\', \'Courier New\', monospace; font-size: 14px; padding: 0.2rem 0.4rem; color: #ffffff; background-color: #212529; border-radius: 0.2rem;\" title=\"sublayer of datalink layer for mac address\">Lower:</kbd>Media access control (MAC)</dd>\r\n<dt style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">Gateway</dt>\r\n<dd style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; margin-left: 0px;\">a device used to connect two different networks, especially a connection to the Internet.</dd>\r\n</dl>', 7, '2020-02-24 15:26:26'),
