(144, 'Javascrip intro and basics', '<h1><strong>Where to write JS code</strong></h1>\r\n<p><strong>1.Inside script Tag inside &lt;head&gt; or &lt;body&gt; or both</strong></p>\r\n<pre class=\"language-markup\"><code>&lt;script&gt;\r\ndocument.getElementById(\"demo\").innerHTML = \"My First JavaScript\";\r\n&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>\r\n<p><strong>2. external javascript, create myScript.js and include inside script tag inside head</strong></p>\r\n<pre class=\"language-markup\"><code>&lt;script src=\"myScript.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Placing scripts at the bottom of the&nbsp; element improves the display speed.</li>\r\n<li>External scripts cannot contain starting and closing script tags</li>\r\n<li>Javascript used to change the behavior of web pages.</li>\r\n<li>JavaScript Can Change HTML Content.</li>\r\n<li>JavaScript Can Change HTML Attribute Values</li>\r\n<li>JavaScript Can Change HTML Styles (CSS)</li>\r\n<li>JavaScript Can Hide/Show HTML Elements&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Basics</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>program</strong> is a list of \"instructions\", these programming instructions are called <strong>statements</strong>.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>JavaScript programs are <strong>executed by</strong> the web browser.</li>\r\n<li>Javascript <strong>statements contains</strong> Values, Operators, Expressions, Keywords, and Comments.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Semicolons</strong> separate JavaScript statements.</li>\r\n<li>JavaScript ignores multiple spaces</li>\r\n<li>JavaScript uses the <strong>var keyword</strong> to declare variables. var x=6; var $xy=6; var _x=6;</li>\r\n<li>it uses lower camel case</li>\r\n<li>JavaScript is Case Sensitive</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>1.Statements</strong></p>\r\n<p>var x, $y, _z;&nbsp; &nbsp; // Statement 1</p>\r\n<p>x = 5;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; // Statement 2 with white spaces</p>\r\n<p>x=x*5; //x*=5;</p>\r\n<p><strong>2.comments</strong></p>\r\n<p>/*this is comment*/</p>\r\n<p>//this is comment</p>\r\n<p><strong>3.concatenation and string</strong></p>\r\n<p>x=x+\" is answer\";</p>\r\n<p>string concatenation in Javascript: var x=\"hello\"+\" \"+\"world\";</p>\r\n<p>If you add a number and a string, the result will be a string!</p>\r\n<p><strong>4.Arithmatic operators</strong></p>\r\n<p>arithmetic operators ( +,&nbsp; -,&nbsp; *,&nbsp; /, %, ** ,++, --, +=, -=, *=,/=)</p>\r\n<p><strong>5.COMPARISON OPERATORS</strong></p>\r\n<p>== equal to</p>\r\n<p>=== if value and type are equal</p>\r\n<p>!=&nbsp; &nbsp; ,&nbsp; &nbsp;!==&nbsp; &nbsp;,&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;&nbsp; &nbsp;,&nbsp; &nbsp; &gt;&nbsp; &nbsp;,&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;=&nbsp; &nbsp;,&nbsp; &nbsp; &gt;=&nbsp; &nbsp;, ?&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>6.LOGICAL OPERATORS:</strong></p>\r\n<p>&amp;&amp;&nbsp; &nbsp; ,&nbsp; &nbsp;||&nbsp; &nbsp; ,&nbsp; &nbsp; !</p>\r\n<p><strong>7.TYPE OPERATORS:</strong></p>\r\n<p>typeof \"John\"&nbsp; ; <strong>//return data type of variable</strong></p>\r\n<p>instanceof <strong>//Returns true if an object is an instance of an object type&nbsp;</strong></p>', 11, '2020-03-26 17:53:59'),
(145, 'Output using javascript', '<p><strong>We can make output using javascript as follows.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&lt;p id=\"demo\"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</p>\r\n<p><strong>1.using innerHTML</strong></p>\r\n<pre class=\"language-markup\"><code>&lt;script&gt;\r\n   document.getElementById(\"demo\").innerHTML = 5 + 6;\r\n&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>\r\n<p><strong>2.using document.write</strong></p>\r\n<pre class=\"language-markup\"><code>&lt;script&gt;\r\n   document.write(5 + 6);\r\n&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>\r\n<p><strong>3.Using alert</strong></p>\r\n<pre class=\"language-markup\"><code>&lt;script&gt;\r\n   window.alert(5 + 6);\r\n&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>\r\n<p><strong>4.Using console</strong></p>\r\n<pre class=\"language-markup\"><code>&lt;script&gt;\r\n   console.log(5 + 6);\r\n&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Using document.write() after an HTML document is loaded, will delete all existing HTML:</p>', 11, '2020-03-26 18:04:51'),
(146, 'Functions in javascript', '<pre class=\"language-markup\"><code>&lt;script&gt;\r\nfunction myFunction(p1, p2) {\r\n  return p1 * p2;\r\n}\r\nalert(myFunction(2,3));\r\n&lt;/script&gt;\r\n\r\n</code></pre>\r\n<p><strong>Function CALLED:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>we can call a function when</strong> an event occurs or calledfrom or direct JavaScript code,Automatically (self invoked).</p>\r\n<p><strong>FUNCATION DEFINATION ACCESS:</strong></p>\r\n<p>function call without <strong>( )</strong> return whole defination of function.</p>\r\n<p>function use local variables, and destroy local variables after execution completes</p>\r\n<p><strong>GLOBAL VARIABLES CAN ALSO BE USED INSIDE FUNCTION</strong></p>', 11, '2020-03-26 18:07:31'),
(147, 'Objects in javascript', '<pre class=\"language-markup\"><code>var person = {\r\n  firstName: \"John\",\r\n  lastName: \"Doe\",\r\n  age: 50,\r\n  eyeColor: \"blue\"\r\n};\r\nconsole.log(person.age);\r\n\r\n</code></pre>\r\n<p>Object use properties ie firstName: \"John\",</p>\r\n<p><strong>ACCESS OBJECTS:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>objectName.propertyName or objectName[\"propertyName\"]</p>\r\n<p>Objects can also use functions.&nbsp;</p>', 11, '2020-03-26 18:09:12'),
(148, 'Events in javascript', '<pre class=\"language-markup\"><code>&lt;html&gt;\r\n   &lt;button onclick=\"document.getElementById(\'demo\').innerHTML = Date()\"&gt;The time is?&lt;/button&gt;\r\n   &lt;button onclick=\"this.innerHTML = Date()\"&gt;The time is?&lt;/button&gt;\r\n   &lt;button onclick=\"alertshow()\"&gt;The time is?&lt;/button&gt;\r\n&lt;script&gt;\r\n   function alertshow(){\r\n      alert(\"done\");\r\n   }\r\n&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/html&gt;\r\n\r\n</code></pre>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; height: 294px;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 21px;\"><strong>MOUSE</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 21px;\"><strong>KEY</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 21px;\"><strong>FORM/INPUT</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 21px;\"><strong>MEDIA</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 21px;\"><strong>CLIPBORD/OTHER</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 21px;\">onclick</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 21px;\">onkeydown</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 21px;\">blur</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 21px;\">pause&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 21px;\">copy</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 21px;\">input</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 21px;\">dblclick</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 21px;\">onchange&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 21px;\">error</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 21px;\">cut</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 21px;\">onmouseout</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 21px;\">keydown</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 21px;\">focusin</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 21px;\">durationchange</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 21px;\">paste</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\r\